": "Do assistance programs affect my interest rate?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Some programs include below-market interest rates as part of the benefit, which obviously helps your rate. Other programs provide grants or second mortgages but don't affect your first mortgage interest rate. A few programs might result in slightly higher rates, but the benefit of the assistance typically outweighs any rate difference."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What if I earn too much for assistance programs?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Income limits exist, but they're often higher than people expect. \"Moderate income\" in many areas includes solid middle-class earnings. Even if you exceed standard program limits, profession-specific programs sometimes have higher limits or no limits at all. Check all available options before assuming you don't qualify."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can self-employed buyers use these programs?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, self-employed buyers can absolutely use first time home buyer programs. You'll need to document your income appropriately (typically through tax returns), but self-employment doesn't disqualify you. Some programs are actually designed to help self-employed individuals who might struggle with conventional financing. Consider bank statement loans if traditional income documentation is challenging."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How do I find programs in my specific state and city?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Start with your state housing finance agency website\u2014search \"[Your State] Housing Finance Agency.\" Then check your city or county housing department website. Contact local nonprofits that offer homebuyer education classes, as they maintain lists of available programs. A knowledgeable mortgage broker can also research programs available in your area."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Are there programs for single parents?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, many programs have no household composition requirements, while some programs specifically target single parents or displaced homemakers. Single parents should check state programs, city programs, nonprofit assistance organizations, and employer benefits. Some areas have programs specifically for single mothers or fathers."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What happens to the assistance if I refinance?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "This depends on your assistance structure. Grants that have met their occupancy requirement typically don't need repayment when you refinance. Second mortgages might need to be paid off in a refinance, or some lenders allow you to keep the second mortgage in place and refinance only the first. Read your assistance program terms carefully before refinancing. An FHA streamline refinance might be possible while maintaining certain types of assistance."}}]};
